-- Beijing Second-Hand Home Sales Fall on Government Curbs, China News Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-10-04T01:53:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-04/beijing-second-hand-home-sales-fall-on-government-curbs-china-news-says.html
Beijing’s second-hand home sales fell
to 18 units on Oct. 1 and Oct. 2 combined, from 1,067 on Sept.
30 alone, after the government and provincial authorities
stepped up measures to cool property prices, China News said.  Home sales in the eastern city of Suzhou dropped to 169
units on Oct. 1 from 519 the day before, and in Hangzhou halved
on Sept. 30 from the previous day, the news service said.  Zhejiang provincial government said it would tighten the
monitoring of developers’ pre-sale funds from November, while
Xiamen of Fujian Province limited new home purchases to one
unit per household until the end of this year, China News
reported.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stanley James at 
 sjames8@bloomberg.net  